<p>Mr. RANDALL. It is a very strange thing that we should pass a bill at the instance of the Department, and that very Department should cause it to be vetoed.</p>
<p>Mr. HOLMAN. A bill prepared at the instance of the Department itself?</p>
<p>Mr. RANDALL. Yes.</p>
<p>Mr. GARFIELD. Let it go to the committee.</p>
